Package com.fizzikgames.fizlib.pathfinding

Utilities for pathfinding in both 2d and 3d grid based space.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AstarHeuristic
    Calculates the heuristic cost of a node for the Astar algorithm
    Mover
    A mover is any object that will be moving with the help of path-finding.
    TileMap
    A tile map is a world that is stored in coordinates referred to as rows or columns, and can even have a depth of traversable layers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Astar
    The Astar pathfinder will implement the Astar algorithm to find the most ideal path from a starting position to an ending position.
    Node
    A node is a point in space that has its own coordinates, and can be used to denote points in both 2d and 3d space.
    Path
    A path is a simple stack of nodes that allows nodes to be added and retrieved in the most useful manner.
